1
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:39,260
Mast! Lay down the mast!

2
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,900
Hurry up and get the rope!

3
00:00:48,220 --> 00:00:50,900
Bow and stern face the banks! Quick!

4
00:00:54,580 --> 00:00:56,980
Thousands of homes are brightly lit,

5
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:59,420
and the doors to them are wide open.

6
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:01,580
This is East Capital.

7
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:05,180
New wine from Sunyang Restaurant!

8
00:01:05,180 --> 00:01:07,700
Welcome to enjoy it!

9
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:10,380
​If you want to know what happens next,

10
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:12,460
wait until next time.

11
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:14,980
People from all over the world gather here,

12
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:17,940
and envoys from various countries come to communicate with the authorities.

13
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:24,660
[Riverside Code at Qingming Festival]

14
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:26,660
[Adapted from Ye Wenbiao's Novel Series of the Same Name]

15
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:27,980
[Episode 22]

16
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:28,980
[Those who are flawless shall remain the same. Those who have minor flaws]

17
00:01:28,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[shall be rectified with measures. - Cheng Hao, Northern Song]

18
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,870
Laoba.

19
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,230
Try to eat something.

20
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:20,390
Laoba.

21
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:26,910
My condolences.

22
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,600
Take good care of yourself.

23
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:45,170
Ban.

24
00:02:48,130 --> 00:02:48,660
My wife

25
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,600
didn't suffer before she died,

26
00:02:52,390 --> 00:02:53,700
right?

27
00:03:04,110 --> 00:03:04,740
No.

28
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,720
Not at all.

29
00:03:18,390 --> 00:03:20,830
She often told me that she wanted

30
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,080
to make lily bulb noodles for you.

31
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:37,290
Good to know that she didn't suffer.

32
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,670
Good to know.

33
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,030
Ban.

34
00:04:14,550 --> 00:04:16,600
Did you come back alone?

35
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,040
Ban.

36
00:04:22,670 --> 00:04:24,730
I dreamed about my mother.

37
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:30,720
What did you dream about?

38
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:32,160
She...

39
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:35,040
She told me

40
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,510
to have proper meals

41
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:40,110
instead of sweets.

42
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:42,200
She told me not to rush

43
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,230
to get undressed when I'm sweating.

44
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:48,720
She told me not to drink too much cold water.

45
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,320
Ban.

46
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,200
My mother

47
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:57,510
won't ever come back, will she?

48
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,270
She will.

49
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,790
Of course, she will.

50
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:07,040
Ban, I miss my mother.

51
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:09,400
She will come back.

52
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:18,460
[Reception Hall for Envoy]

53
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:19,280
That's right.

54
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,600
This is the place.

55
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:21,640
I remember it.

56
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,390
Okay.

57
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,230
Father.

58
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,720
I'll talk to Envoy Cui.

59
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:27,110
Pay attention.

60
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,550
If they speak in a foreign language,

61
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,880
tell me what they're saying.

62
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:30,640
Oh no.

63
00:05:31,530 --> 00:05:32,980
I forgot everything.

64
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:35,230
How come?

65
00:05:35,230 --> 00:05:36,510
You said you could understand.

66
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:38,670
I haven't spoken to foreigners for years.

67
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:40,160
I forgot.

68
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:40,830
Then

69
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,270
go home first.

70
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:42,880
I'll be back soon.

71
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:43,760
I'm not going home.

72
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,760
I've come all the way.

73
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:45,540
Stop messing around.

74
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,890
Let me take a look.

75
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,600
I haven't been here for ages.

76
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,950
H-Hide first.

77
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:50,550
Okay.

78
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:51,390
I'll take you home later.

79
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,040
Okay.

80
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,370
Clean it well.

81
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:06,110
This is the Sparrow Lane.

82
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:08,320
Take a seat.

83
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,720
You'll live at Xi's place from now on.

84
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,760
Xi is Ban's good friend.

85
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,440
She lives next door to us.

86
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:22,580
Thank you.

87
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,440
What for?

88
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:26,370
We should thank you

89
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,200
for saving Ban.

90
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:31,230
Come to us whenever you need anything.

91
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:33,000
Try to recover first.

92
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,830
Here, take one.

93
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,670
It's freshly picked.

94
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:43,790
Thanks.

95
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:57,480
Everything

96
00:06:57,830 --> 00:06:59,000
looks so unreal.

97
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:06,640
For someone who just escaped the dark days,

98
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,160
it may seem unreal.

99
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,670
They may be scared

100
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,790
that it is a dream they'd wake up from.

101
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:19,880
You'll get used to it.

102
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:23,760
There will be no more filth in your life.

103
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,440
You'll live an ordinary life.

104
00:07:34,670 --> 00:07:37,350
What is an ordinary life?

105
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,210
You'll get to find out.

106
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:43,110
Mrs. Zhao.

107
00:07:45,950 --> 00:07:47,720
I wanted to pick you up there

108
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,550
but missed you.

109
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,070
You must be Wu Mei.

110
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,230
Xi, sorry for the trouble.

111
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:54,230
Don't mention it.

112
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,670
Your friends

113
00:07:55,670 --> 00:07:57,070
are my friends.

114
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,320
Come on, Mei.

115
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,270
Let's go home.

116
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,000
Let me help you.

117
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:04,550
Let's go.

118
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:06,040
Be careful.

119
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:19,740
[Reception Hall for Envoy]

120
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,070
What can I

121
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,230
do for you?

122
00:08:29,670 --> 00:08:31,200
You must be Envoy Cui.

123
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,520
I'm Zhao Buyou

124
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,030
from the Kaifeng Court.

125
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:38,910
I know your secrets.

126
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:41,640
What secrets?

127
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,280
Your barrels.

128
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:44,760
What barrels?

129
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,520
Stop playing dumb.

130
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,470
Where is Luan Hui?

131
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,350
I don't know what you are talking about.

132
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,960
Load the ship overnight.

133
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,670
We're going home.

134
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:56,320
What?

135
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,280
Buyou.

136
00:08:57,550 --> 00:08:58,350
Buyou.

137
00:08:59,320 --> 00:08:59,910
Father.

138
00:09:00,470 --> 00:09:01,470
What was he saying?

139
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,760
He told them to load the goods

140
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,590
and rush back home overnight.

141
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,640
You've got the nerves.

142
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,320
You're planning to abscond?

143
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:21,880
Get up.

144
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,710
You got the wrong person.

145
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,280
I look like him, right?

146
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:29,590
Yeah.

147
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,360
So similar.

148
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:32,840
Father.

149
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:33,930
Who did he think you were?

150
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,080
We do look alike.

151
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,970
But I'm much more handsome.

152
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,150
Yeah.

153
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:47,280
So similar.

154
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:48,420
We know

155
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,010
everything you're doing.

156
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,230
Since you're here,

157
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,440
admire our integrity and spirit

158
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,110
of the Great Song.

159
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,680
Stop sneaking around

160
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,000
and doing illegal things.

161
00:10:01,740 --> 00:10:02,920
It's not the right path.

162
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:04,760
Don't you want to go home?

163
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,200
Then what should I do?

164
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:11,730
What...?

165
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,200
Listen.

166
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:16,530
You're encircled by the officers of the Kaifeng Court.

167
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,520
Don't even think about going home

168
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,890
if you don't confess.

169
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,200
Do you hear me?

170
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:27,680
I did meet Mr. Luan Hui again.

171
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:31,470
I told him that I was preparing to go home.

172
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:32,880
He

173
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,000
paid me three times the money

174
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,280
for a barrel.

175
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,110
He paid for your barrel?

176
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,550
We're here?

177
00:10:59,200 --> 00:10:59,960
Yeah.

178
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,790
So soon?

179
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,960
Mr. Luan.

180
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,320
Some text

181
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:19,570
is not very clear in your account book.

182
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,140
We brought you here

183
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:23,120
for clarification.

184
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:35,760
Wen Yue.

185
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,550
Buyou said

186
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:38,470
he'd bring you home tomorrow night.

187
00:11:38,590 --> 00:11:40,000
Why wait until tomorrow?

188
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,960
Just stay tonight.

189
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:45,080
There is still work at the umbrella shop.

190
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,960
Don't come with me.

191
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,910
Help Su settle in

192
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,200
at Mrs. Lan's place.

193
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:51,760
Wen Yue.

194
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,470
I gave Su away to Mrs. Lan.

195
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,550
Am I being irresponsible?

196
00:11:57,110 --> 00:12:00,320
You went into danger to help Su find her mother.

197
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,960
How are you irresponsible?

198
00:12:02,590 --> 00:12:05,080
It's just that Mrs. Lan is more experienced with kids.

199
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:07,960
And it's good news that Mrs. Lan

200
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,080
wants to adopt Su.

201
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,730
You are still a child yourself.

202
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,610
Don't be too harsh on yourself.

203
00:12:15,690 --> 00:12:16,240
Go back.

204
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,640
Wen Yue.

205
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,640
You're right.

206
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:23,110
Mrs. Lan is all by herself.

207
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,280
She won't be so lonely with Su around.

208
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,400
Besides, we live so close to each other.

209
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,840
Whenever Su misses us,

210
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:31,530
she can come over for fun.

211
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,960
And I believe

212
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:35,550
that a family doesn't have to be

213
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,550
bound by blood.

214
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,150
Wherever there is love, there is home.

215
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,000
Right?

216
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:43,670
You have really grown up.

217
00:12:45,150 --> 00:12:46,350
Thank you, Wen Yue.

218
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,790
I used to feel sorry for myself.

219
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,200
I thought I was pitiful

220
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:53,230
because I had never seen my mother.

221
00:12:53,470 --> 00:12:54,880
But later, I found out

222
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,610
that there are many poor people

223
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:57,380
in this world.

224
00:12:57,930 --> 00:12:59,450
Just like Su

225
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,280
and Mr. He

226
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,440
who was locked up with me.

227
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:06,550
What about him?

228
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:09,000
He told me

229
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:11,150
that his father used to be a boat builder

230
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,400
by Taihu Lake.

231
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,550
One day, a villain broke into their home

232
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,840
and killed his parents.

233
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:19,280
And his older sister went missing.

234
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,670
His surname is He, right?

235
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:28,150
What else did he say?

236
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,670
He said

237
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:31,150
that his original surname

238
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:33,110
was Su, and not He.

239
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,550
Wait for me.

240
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,440
Come on.

241
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,180
Pass it.

242
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,150
Catch it.

243
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,350
Aren't you the sister who saved us?

244
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:02,000
Little girl, is Mr. He here?

245
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:04,910
He was here just now.

246
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:07,440
Should I take you to wait for him in his room?

247
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,550
Okay.

248
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,470
Here.

249
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:18,350
Sister.

250
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:20,230
This is Mr. He's room.

251
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:22,000
Please wait for him here.

252
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,230
I'll go back to playing.

253
00:14:23,350 --> 00:14:24,520
Okay, thank you.

254
00:15:13,110 --> 00:15:14,080
Lady Wen, be careful.

255
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,150
This Mahoraga figure has been broken once.

256
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,650
I glued it up.

257
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:22,110
This is yours?

258
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:23,880
Yeah.

259
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,030
My big sister made it for me.

260
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,590
She said that one was her

261
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:28,590
and the other

262
00:15:28,590 --> 00:15:29,440
was me.

263
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,080
How did it

264
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:36,080
break?

265
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:41,670
Sorry.

266
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,740
I don't mean to pry.

267
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,280
I don't mind telling you.

268
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:05,030
It's just that it broke

269
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:07,670
when I lost my loved one.

270
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,110
One night when I was a child,

271
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,710
a villain broke into our house.

272
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:18,960
I saw him

273
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,670
killing my parents.

274
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,670
I rushed forward to bite him.

275
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,400
The Mahoraga figure

276
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,150
broke at that moment.

277
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:34,000
I was too young

278
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:35,880
to beat him.

279
00:16:37,470 --> 00:16:39,000
He threw me to the side

280
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:41,030
and I passed out.

281
00:16:42,110 --> 00:16:43,550
I woke up

282
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,150
only to learn from the authorities

283
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:49,500
that my sister had gone missing

284
00:16:50,550 --> 00:16:51,790
and my parents

285
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:53,890
were dead.

286
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:02,520
Actually,

287
00:17:05,230 --> 00:17:06,400
I also made a Mahoraga figure

288
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,280
for my brother when I was young.

289
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:11,110
It looked just like this one.

290
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:14,190
But I hadn't had time to color it.

291
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,400
My Mahoraga figure

292
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:18,830
wasn't colored, either.

293
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:20,640
I colored it myself.

294
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,680
Over the years,

295
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,920
whenever I see it,

296
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,800
I tell myself

